By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has released COVID-19 update for Sunday saying that 304 new infections were recorded in 14 states and FCT.With this, the total confirmed cases of coronavirus in the country is now 43,841 out of which 20,308 have been discharged. However, the infection has claimed 888 lives, NCDC said. Lagos recorded 81 of the 304 cases, followed by FCT with 39, Abia with 31 and Kaduna 24.The rest are: “Rivers-23, Plateau-16, Cross River-13, Ebonyi-12, Ondo-12, Ekiti-11, Edo-11, Benue-10, Nasarawa-10, Ogun-6, Gombe-5”The total confirmed cases so far in Nigeria now stands at 43,841 of which 20,308 have been discharged. The report reads: Lagos-81FCT-39Abia-31Kaduna-24Rivers-23Plateau-16Cross River-13Ebonyi-12Ondo-12Ekiti-11Edo-11Benue-10Nasarawa-10Ogun-6Gombe-5 Furthermore, the breakdown of cases by states is shown below: By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has recorded 404  new COVID-19 cases in the country, as total infections from the virus rise to 42,208. The NCDC made this known on its official twitter handle on Wednesday. The health agency noted that five more persons… July 30, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - Nigeria has recorded 544 new COVID-19 cases, a development which has taken the country’s total infection tally to 28,711. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) disclosed this on its official twitter handle on Sunday. NCDC said that as of July, 5. 2020, 544  new… July 6, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Nigeria Monday announced 229 new confirmed cases of COVID-19 with  seven deaths while the total number of patients discharged so far stand at 2,311, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has reported. The NCDC which released the report on its official twitter handle  informed… May 26, 2020 In "Top Stories"